To create a footnote for the authors list in LaTeX, use the \footnotemark command followed by a \footnote command in the authors list. Make sure the corresponding footnotes are placed at the bottom of the page using the \footnotetext command. Here's an example:

```latex
\documentclass{article}
\usepackage[bottom]{footmisc}

\begin{document}

\author{Author A$^\ast$}
\author{Author B$^\dagger$}
\author{Author C}

\title{Title}

\maketitle

\footnotetext[1]{$^\ast$Corresponding author.}
\footnotetext[2]{$^\dagger$This author contributed equally to this work.}

\end{document}
```
